headline: Nipocalimab demonstrates significant clinical improvement in disease activity and IgG reduction in Phase 2 Sjögren's disease study
summary: Johnson & Johnson (NYSE: JNJ) today announced results from additional analyses of the Phase 2 DAHLIAS study highlighting improvement in key measures of disease activity and significant IgG reduction by over 77% following treatment with investigational nipocalimab in adult patients with moderate-to-severe Sjögren's disease (SjD).
